Good news for prostate cancer patients in Gauteng who don’t have medical aid. A first-of-its-kind prostate cancer procedure has been introduced in the public health sector. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Good news for prostate cancer patients in Gauteng who don’t have medical aid. A first-of-its-kind prostate cancer procedure has been introduced in the public health sector. READ: Immunotherapy approved for use in fight against cancer Prostate brachytherapy is a treatment that can be used alone to treat early-stage prostate cancer It involves patients having tiny radioactive seeds inserted into their prostates via an ultrasound probe. Masego Rahlaga shares more details in the video above.